---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'In what model do you sell this? Body leasing?',
    a: 'Fixed-scope Professional Services. Small teams of two to four staff engineers committed to a concrete outcome - not time-and-materials per head. We are not a body-leasing shop: we do not place juniors under your PM and call it delivery.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How much time does my team need to commit?',
    a: 'Rough guidance: Phase 1 takes roughly four hours per week for two weeks from two or three people (tech lead, SRE, security). Phase 2 asks for one engineer on your side as an embedded partner, close to full-time, with the rest of the team async. By Phase 3 the roles flip - your platform team drives, we assist on request.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the typical ROI and when do we see it?',
    a: 'First signal usually lands six to eight weeks in, once the pilot team is shipping on the new setup. Full-rollout ROI tends to surface at six to nine months. We do not ship a ROI calculator - we measure cycle time, PR merge time and build time before the pilot and again after, and the report is part of the engagement.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What technologies do you support?',
    a: 'Our deepest experience is in the JVM world - Scala, Kotlin, Java, Bazel, sbt, Gradle. Most of the platform components are tech-agnostic and have been deployed against Python, TypeScript and Go stacks as well. If your stack is unusual, ask - we will tell you up front what we have and have not shipped against.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you keep access to our code or infrastructure after the engagement?',
    a: 'No. All credentials are revoked at the end of the engagement. The code stays with you - we do not keep a copy of your repository. If you want a retainer (Phase 4), we sign a new NDA and contract for that scope.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can we use just one component, or buy it outright?',
    a: 'All six components are open source under the MIT licence - clone the repo, read the code, ship it yourself. You only pay us for the work: integration into your stack, hardening, capability transfer. There is no per-seat licence and no lock-in on the components themselves.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where do the -88% and -43% numbers come from?',
    a: 'Both are from VirtusLab client engagements. The -88% build-time figure comes from a global logistics company where we migrated a Scala monorepo from sbt to Bazel (40-60 minutes down to around 5). The -43% PR merge time comes from an investment bank running a managed IntelliJ IDEA solution on a Scala monorepo. Clients are under NDA. Full write-ups live on the VirtusLab success stories page.',
  },
];
---
<section id="faq" class="section section-alt faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="fade-up mb-10">
      <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Questions we hear before we start</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Straight answers to the questions procurement, platform leads and engineering directors actually ask us on the first call.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((item, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item fade-up" name="faq" open={i === 0}>
          <summary>
            <span class="faq-q">{item.q}</span>
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">{item.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="faq-footnote">
      Not here? Email <a href="mailto:visdom@virtuslab.com">visdom@virtuslab.com</a> - an engineer will reply within one business day.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-section {
    padding-top: 5rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 52rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease;
  }

  .faq-item[open] {
    border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.35);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-q {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .faq-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .faq-icon::before,
  .faq-icon::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    background: var(--color-emerald);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-icon::before {
    top: 50%;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 2px;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
  }

  .faq-icon::after {
    left: 50%;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-icon::after {
    transform: translateX(-50%) scaleY(0);
  }

  .faq-a {
    margin: 0.9rem 0 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .faq-footnote {
    margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .faq-footnote a {
    color: var(--color-emerald-dark, var(--color-emerald));
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
